order=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f106351143098705>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: Grouping Rants</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Sep 13th 11:54 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=147821><span id=Sage>Aggrok</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>266 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.60]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;   I'd like to thank whoever for bagging my post. I really dont care about my rating , but as I said in the very first line if you dont like rants then stop reading. Apparently I need to clarify a few things. To those who know the things Im about to write please bear with me.<br><br>  Im not a PoV expert, but Ive been there enough to know what to do. I started in PoT /ooc'ing for a group that had to have the following: all members 58+, a chanter, a cleric, and some decent melee ability. With the group I listed, I got all 3 and even tho we are all a bit low for PoV, I felt we had an excellent group.<br><br>   I was the group leader, which means you listen to me, loot the way in which I say, and fight at the camp I want to go. If you dont like these rules, then dont join the group. I wasn't on a power trip or anything, and when I join others' groups, I fight at the camp they want and do loot the way they want. Its give and take. Personally I dislike being GL as its too taxing and I'd rather group with more experienced people as thats the best way to learn. Its generally accepted ( atleast the way I learned ) that if you have less than 2 hours to play, then you either let the group know from the outset or dont join. Many times other players are passed up to accept you into a group and they might have had 8 hours to play. These people aren't going to wait around hoping a spot will open up, they join/make other groups or leave the zone. Its unfair to me to make a group suffer while looking for another member to fill your spot. Announce to the group atleast 15 minutes before you have to leave so they can find someone to replace you.<br><br>  There is a big difference between honest mistakes and blatant stupidity. Mistakes include targetting the wrong member for a heal, mistiming a heal, misjudging pulling distances and getting an add, etc. Everyone does these from time to time and I never get upset about this stuff, even if it results in my death. However, purposely ignoring your group leader and deciding you want to camp a different camp is unacceptable. Inner camp is a bit tougher that outer and as it were we didn't have the DPS to handle the tougher mobs. Trying to retrieve a corpse while your party is engaged in a fight is unacceptable. Camping out and not returning in the middle of a fight with 5 rezzes to do is unacceptable. If you pull this kind of crap in a raid expect to be disbanded immediately. That behavior is the stuff that causes total raid wipes. Perhaps you thought I was harsh on my group but Im not dying for a group that doesnt listen and pulls that kind of childish behaviour. <br><br>I cant see for the life of me why we had 3 level 58+ melees and they argued for 5 minutes on who was to pull. By that level they should all be excellent pullers. I solo alot and learned to pull as a pure caster and the only reasons I didnt pull myself was that I was on a horse ( he's slow ) and I had a pet up, which we needed for DPS.  <br><br>I forgot to mention in one other PoV group one of the members was looting everything as it dropped, and after about 10 loots I asked politely if he could spread the looting around. After 5 more mobs looted in a row I told the group I was leaving as soon as they got a replacement. I am not rich and yes a 15 or 20pp item makes a difference to me. Most groups I know either do a FFA loot on cheaper stuff, and random the higher stuff like nice items and spell drops. Sometimes a group will state from the beginning that so-and-so is master looter and loot will be sold and plat split at the end. Either way is fair, but hording all the kills will piss off 5 other people. Its hard enough to get groups sometimes with a good reputation, cant imagine it with a bad one.<br><br>I make sure to thank/congratulate a group when you beat a really tough mob or come thru on a horrible pull. A small thank-you can go a long way with people and being friendly will go 10 times a far as being an a$$. When loot is lotto'ed I congratulate the winner. When I leave a group I get a replacement before I go so it doesnt slow them down. A melee class leaving a group isnt so devastating, but if you dont have a enchanter or beastlord and you are the only shaman then guess what? Your group now has no slower. No group is going to surive long in a tier 2+ plane without slows. Even a group with 2 clerics will have more downtime than a group with one cleric/ one shaman. Turgurs Insects is a 75% slow at 60+, meaning that mobs with it only attack 25% as fast. Without it they  do 4 times the damage requiring 4 times the heals.<br><br><br>In the end I'd like to say if you don't agree with what I say thats fine, but don't tank someones rating without offering an alternative way to do something. If no one posts their opinions then no one can learn anything new here and we all lose.<br><br>61 Ogre Oracle on Luclin server--Chaotic Winds--Venerable Aggrok</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
